          "durationMs": 7000
        },
        {
          "trigger": "step_1",
          "text": "Acacia trees communicate via airborne chemicals.\nWhen one is grazed, it releases tannins — and signals neighbours to do the same.\nPlants invented chemical warfare first.",
          "durationMs": 8000
